{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1093ad0a-c93a-4641-9726-bc9c42c00ef7","content":"You already have the HotReload extension referenced. To use it, run your tests with the `--hotreload` flag:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --hotreload\n```\n\nThis starts the test runner in a watch-like mode. When it detects source changes (you save a file), it **re-runs the tests without a full rebuild** — applying hot-reload deltas instead. The workflow is:\n\n1. Run `dotnet test --hotreload`\n2. See which tests fail\n3. Edit your code/tests and save\n4. Tests re-run automatically with your changes applied\n\nIt's much faster than a full `dotnet test` cycle since it skips the rebuild step. Press `Ctrl+C` to exit when done.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"08fef96b-7797-419e-9375-22be7b8ab1cd","outputTokens":170,"requestId":"EC59:30C599:3316E4F:388C7B2:6A02FA4E"},"id":"f9a80c94-c075-4dd4-b2b3-ab00ab3d2a95","timestamp":"2026-05-12T10:00:52.804Z","parentId":"72ab3d2f-0139-4340-ac61-6f7ff880cfce"}
